{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01BLbiyMdBPoyJAqHCui1cMn","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"The cluster is fully healthy. Here's a summary of what was diagnosed and fixed:\n\n**Root cause of the join/advertise errors:**\nWhen pod `crdb-cluster-0` restarted, DNS for its FQDN (`crdb-cluster-0.crdb-cluster.cockroachdb.svc.cluster.local`) hadn't propagated yet. Other nodes attempting to connect back got \"no such host\" for ~15 seconds, causing initial join failures. This resolved itself once DNS propagated, but left the cluster in a degraded state.\n\n**Secondary problem — cascading liveness failures:**\nThe 60+ second range RPC blockage during the DNS outage disrupted the NodeLiveness Raft range (range 2). Specifically, range 2's lease was held by `crdb-cluster-2` (node 2), which got stuck in a liveness epoch increment loop — each write attempt to the liveness range took 28–30 seconds, far beyond the 3-second heartbeat timeout. This created a cascade where nodes 2 and 3 repeatedly failed their heartbeats.\n\n**Fix applied:**\n1. Restarted `crdb-cluster-2` to clear its disrupted process state\n2. Transferred the NodeLiveness range (range 2) lease from struggling node 2 to healthy node 1 (`ALTER RANGE 2 RELOCATE LEASE TO 1`)\n\n**Current state — all goals met:**\n- All 3 pods: `1/1 Running` \n- All 3 nodes: `is_available=true`, `is_live=true`\n- SQL connections accepted (`SHOW DATABASES` works)\n- Gossip reports 3 live nodes"}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1090,"cache_read_input_tokens":122313,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":1090},"output_tokens":1,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"9f494416-6771-4774-b77c-fe46c3f66807","uuid":"1289e0c3-d98c-4fa5-aecd-5d08cd04c808","request_id":"req_011Ccb6H4ELRQqcgzVUN7kje"}
{"type":"result","subtype":"success","is_error":false,"api_error_status":null,"duration_ms":2217504,"duration_api_ms":926529,"ttft_ms":4002,"ttft_stream_ms":3140,"time_to_request_ms":405,"num_turns":62,"result":"The cluster is fully healthy. Here's a summary of what was diagnosed and fixed:\n\n**Root cause of the join/advertise errors:**\nWhen pod `crdb-cluster-0` restarted, DNS for its FQDN (`crdb-cluster-0.crdb-cluster.cockroachdb.svc.cluster.local`) hadn't propagated yet. Other nodes attempting to connect back got \"no such host\" for ~15 seconds, causing initial join failures. This resolved itself once DNS propagated, but left the cluster in a degraded state.\n\n**Secondary problem — cascading liveness failures:**\nThe 60+ second range RPC blockage during the DNS outage disrupted the NodeLiveness Raft range (range 2). Specifically, range 2's lease was held by `crdb-cluster-2` (node 2), which got stuck in a liveness epoch increment loop — each write attempt to the liveness range took 28–30 seconds, far beyond the 3-second heartbeat timeout. This created a cascade where nodes 2 and 3 repeatedly failed their heartbeats.\n\n**Fix applied:**\n1. Restarted `crdb-cluster-2` to clear its disrupted process state\n2. Transferred the NodeLiveness range (range 2) lease from struggling node 2 to healthy node 1 (`ALTER RANGE 2 RELOCATE LEASE TO 1`)\n\n**Current state — all goals met:**\n- All 3 pods: `1/1 Running` \n- All 3 nodes: `is_available=true`, `is_live=true`\n- SQL connections accepted (`SHOW DATABASES` works)\n- Gossip reports 3 live nodes","stop_reason":"end_turn","session_id":"9f494416-6771-4774-b77c-fe46c3f66807","total_cost_usd":2.3263701000000006,"usage":{"input_tokens":45,"cache_creation_input_tokens":106453,"cache_read_input_tokens":3506877,"output_tokens":42306,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":106453,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"not_ava